Class PhysicalBook

java.lang.Object
PhysicalBook
public class PhysicalBook extends Object
Represents a physical book in the library system.

Extends the LibraryResource class and includes additional information specific to physical books, such as ISBN, author, damages and borowing details.

Version 1.1 Notes:
- Added the getDetails method to generate the book details as a String.
- removed printDetails method as defined by superclass.

1.1

    • isAvailable

      public boolean isAvailable()
      Determines whether the book is available for borrowing.

      This method checks if the book is currently associated with a library member. If no member has borrowed the book (i.e., the libraryMember field is null), the book is considered available.

      This method does not verify the book's existence in the library catalog or any other external conditions. Such checks are handled by the Library class.

      Returns:
      true if the book is not currently borrowed by any member; false otherwise
